3181	\begin{lemma}[Slice-presentation transport for quasi-coherence data]
3182	  \label{lem:quasicoherentData_bind_mathlib}
3183	  \lean{SheafOfModules.QuasicoherentData.bind}
3184	  \mathlibok
3185	  \textit{Provided by Mathlib (\texttt{Mathlib.Algebra.Category.ModuleCat.Sheaf.Quasicoherent}).}
3186	  Mathlib's \(\mathrm{QuasicoherentData.bind}\) transports a presentation across an iterated
3187	  Grothendieck slice: from quasi-coherence data on a cover \(\{X_i\}\) and, for each \(i\), data on a
3188	  cover of \(M.\mathrm{over}\,X_i\), it assembles quasi-coherence data on the composite cover, by
3189	  applying \(\mathrm{Presentation.map}\) (\cref{lem:presentation_map_mathlib}) along the equivalence
3190	  \(\mathrm{pushforwardPushforwardEquivalence}(\mathrm{Over.iteratedSliceEquiv}\,\cdots)\). It is the
3191	  worked template for the per-element presentation transport used in \cref{lem:over_restrict_iso} and
3192	  \cref{lem:isIso_fromTildeΓ_basicOpen_of_quasicoherent}, handling the slice-site adjointness and
3193	  sheafification typeclass synthesis.
3194	\end{lemma}
